Here’s how you can make your **Form2** “Search” button jump into the right ATP folder based on `BenchTypeValue`.

---

### 1. Pass `BenchTypeValue` into Form2

In **Form1**, wherever you do

```csharp
Form2 ConfAutoDialog = new Form2();
```

change it to

```csharp
Form2 ConfAutoDialog = new Form2(this.BenchTypeValue);
```

and add an overload on your **Form2**:

```csharp
public partial class Form2 : Form
{
    private readonly string _benchTypeValue;

    // New ctor:
    public Form2(string benchTypeValue)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        _benchTypeValue = benchTypeValue;
    }

    // … your existing ctor(Form2()) can forward into this one if you like:
    public Form2() : this("Default") { }
}
```

---

### 2. In Form2, wire up the Search‐button

Suppose your “Search” button is called `buttonSearch`, and you have a TextBox called `textBoxLink` to receive the folder. In Form2 add:

```csharp
using System.IO;
using System.Windows.Forms;

public partial class Form2 : Form
{
    // … your existing members …

    private void buttonSearch_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        using (var folderDlg = new FolderBrowserDialog())
        {
            // decide default folder name
            string baseDir = Application.StartupPath; // or wherever you keep your ATP folders
            string sub = _benchTypeValue switch
            {
                "PC12" => "ATP12",
                "PC21" => "ATP21",
                _      => "ATP"
            };

            string defaultPath = Path.Combine(baseDir, sub);
            // if it doesn’t exist, FolderBrowserDialog will just show the nearest parent
            folderDlg.SelectedPath = defaultPath;

            if (folderDlg.ShowDialog(this) == DialogResult.OK)
            {
                textBoxLink.Text = folderDlg.SelectedPath;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

---

#### What this does

- **Form1** now tells **Form2** which bench you’re on.
- **Form2** stores that in `_benchTypeValue`.
- When the user clicks **Search**, we pick the right subfolder name (`ATP12`, `ATP21` or `ATP`) and pre‐seed the `FolderBrowserDialog` there.

That way, for PC12 benches you start browsing in **…\ATP12**, for PC21 in **…\ATP21**, otherwise in **…\ATP**.
